# Every path needs a maintainer's review. The registry's only real defence is that a human read the
# module before it merged: the checksum proves the bytes did not change in transit, not that they
# were ever safe (R-6).
*                   @zlexdev

# These three decide what the whole registry means, so they are called out separately rather than
# left to the catch-all above. index.json is generated on main and must never merge from a PR;
# authors.yml is an identity roster; .github/ is the CI that enforces the rest.
/index.json         @zlexdev
/authors.yml        @zlexdev
/.github/           @zlexdev
